I 1482 fordrev han sin far Abu al-Hasan Ali, men ble selv slått og fanget av Ferdinand den katolske. snippets.snippet: Wu wei (Chinese: 無 爲; pinyin: wú wéi) is a concept literally meaning "inexertion", "inaction", or "effortless action". Wu wei emerged in the Spring and Autumn period, and from Confucianism, to become an important concept in Chinese statecraft and Taoism, and was most commonly used to refer to an ideal form of government, including the behavior of the emperor.
